=================================================================================
                        VIDEO SCALER ARCHITECTURE ANALYSIS
=================================================================================

Input Video Specifications:
  Format: 1280x720 @ 60Hz (720p)
  Pixel clock: 74.25 MHz (DDR interpolated as 148.5 MHz)
  Pixel bandwidth: 1.78 Gbps

Output Video Specifications:
  Format: 1920x1080 @ 60Hz (1080p)
  Pixel clock: 148.5 MHz
  Pixel bandwidth: 2.97 Gbps
  Scaling ratio: 1.5x vertical (720 to 1080 lines)

Processing Pipeline:
  Input register stage:     1 cycle
  Line buffer access:       variable (1-2 cycles)
  Interpolation:            2 cycles (bilinear)
  Output register:          1 cycle
  Total latency:            4-5 lines

Line Buffer Utilization:
  720p input line:          1280 pixels x 24-bit = 30.72 Kbits
  Storage needed:           2 lines (for interpolation) = 61.44 Kbits
  Allocated:                4 EBR blocks = 72 Kbits
  Utilization:             85.3%

Interpolation Resources:
  Operations per pixel:     8 multiplications (RGB x3 channels + blending)
  DSP blocks used:          8 x 18x18 multipliers
  Throughput:               1 pixel/cycle @ 148.5 MHz = 148.5 Mpixel/s


