=================================================================================
                        CRITICAL DESIGN NOTES
=================================================================================

High-Speed Video Design Considerations:
  1. Pixel clock at 148.5 MHz requires careful PCB layout
  2. LVDS differential pairs for video data reduce EMI
  3. Timing slack is only 0.687 ns - very tight for production
  4. Line buffers consume significant EBR resources (4 blocks)

Optimization Opportunities:
  1. Register pipelining can improve Fmax to 200+ MHz
  2. Dedicated DSP blocks for interpolation are efficient
  3. Can support higher resolution with register insertions
  4. Unused DSP blocks (232) available for future expansion

Production Concerns:
  1. Timing closure is marginal - requires careful implementation
  2. Thermal management important at 234.5 mW dissipation
  3. Recommend extensive timing analysis before tape-out
  4. Temperature derating analysis needed (up to 125°C operation)


=================================================================================
                        RECOMMENDATIONS
=================================================================================

For Timing Improvement:
  1. Add register stage after line buffer for Fmax → 200+ MHz
     Cost: +2 pipeline stages (acceptable for 60Hz video)
  2. Optimize interpolator logic with retiming
  3. Use dedicated routing resources for video buses

For Power Reduction:
  1. Reduce I/O drive strength where possible
  2. Implement clock gating for interpolator during sync blanking
  3. Optimize DSP block utilization

For Scalability:
  1. Design supports 4Kx2K with register insertion
  2. Can pipeline for real-time effects (color correction, etc.)
  3. Spare DSP blocks available for motion estimation


